The paper presents a new dataset for benchmark evaluation of methods in the reading comprehension task, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the performance of state-of-the-art models, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the dataset may be useful for information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC) research.
